OL,5, England and Wales are less ethnically  
OL,6, segregated than they have ever been,   
OL,7, according to a new study.              
OL,9,FResearchers looked at thousands of     
OL,10,Fneighbourhoods across the two nations, 
OL,11,Falongside data from the 2021 census.   
OL,13,FThey found that more people from       
OL,14,Fdifferent ethnic backgrounds are now   
OL,15,Fliving close to each other or next door
OL,16,Fto each other than ever recorded.      
OL,18,FStudy author Dr Gemma Catney told BBC  
OL,19,FNews the data suggests people are      
OL,20,Fgenerally becoming more tolerant.      
